document.title: Indiana Department of Education College and Career Readiness

CC3B734940EC43C289B28BDFEC4E77DC.description:
Formulate and present a position or course of action on an issue by examining the underlying factors
contributing to that issue and support that position.

680EACCB825D4933BC478B1EC5BB6994.description:
Use technology in the process of conducting historical research and to present products of historical
research.

583C794E32D1456C90D2195DAAD18282.description:
Explain issues and problems of the past by analyzing various interests and viewpoints of the participants
involved.

604B64F19065468BBC81EDD9C7079DCB.description:
Investigate and interpret multiple causation in analyzing historical actions and analyze cause-and-effect
relationships.

D081A530803E4E7FBD22F1DCCBDEC702.description: Locate and analyze primary sources and secondary sources related to an event or issue of the past.

73360E5056BD4D6490B347FA2B54DC8C.description:
Identify patterns of historical change and duration and construct a representation that illustrates continuity
and change.

694CDD06EB284713938A3CDEC7621714.description: Investigate current global issues such as terrorism, genocide, and environmental issues.

3C717B510DFC4BA796487B08C3B27902.description: Describe and analyze the global expansion of democracy and globalization in the late 20th century.

2486F5DF3F5848AB85B5377C705DA920.description:
Trace the rise of communism in China including its foundations, the Cultural Revolution, and
 modern day developments.

6A3363EAA41245C4AA1572C78612DC28.description: Explain the origins of the modern State of Israel.

923B3635E1324EFF9E3E51043D19A030.description:
Describe the paths to decolonization and independence from colonial rule in Asia, Africa, and the Middle
East.

64C6A94EF0174C8688D576F213E83000.description:
Explain the causes and consequences of the Cold War and describe the role it played in ethnic or
nationalistic conflicts in various parts of the world.

B8120919F8EA4834B533D4A2F7692507.description:
Examine the causes, course, and effects of the Holocaust including accounts of camp inmates, survivors,
 liberators, and perpetrators; and, summarize world responses including the Nuremberg Trials.

C5C4DA1086374179A3EF6F95AA8FF999.description:
Identify the causes and key events of World War II and analyze the impact this war had on the global
community.

722EC31C45AE43C99F2D386698046AE5.description:
Examine the events and developments of the interwar period and their impact on the beginning of WWII
including the impact of WWI on society, the Great Depression, and the rise of totalitarianism.

8CC011D54BC147CA99817655A06E0BD0.description:
Explain the causes and consequences of the Russian Revolutions of 1917 and the establishment of the
Union of Soviet Socialist Republics.

CCF11345E09E42BDB763644458F3590F.description:
Trace and explain the long-term and immediate causes (including Nationalism, Imperialism, Militarism, and
Alliances), major events and global consequences of World War I.

4BDC198BF34B45DBB4032237AB7ECA18.description: An Era of Global Conflicts, Challenges, Controversies, and Changes: 1900 CE to the Present

AF3D2D6321D747E3AB8D608BB782964E.description: Compare and contrast the responses of China and Japan to challenges by Western imperial powers.

5A68572AB7A2432BBA0217FF10885132.description:
Analyze the causes and consequences of European imperialism upon the indigenous peoples of Africa, Asia
and Oceania.

5C9A7AB27B9F46F4B86B0D4BB7FD7C0B.description:
Examine the economic, social, and political changes caused by the Industrial Revolution and their impact on
the development of political and economic theory.

96332173DB2B412B96858338F0D4FEE5.description: Explain the causes and conditions of the Industrial Revolution in England, Europe, and the United States.

1A93536FEF5547249E1DD03228164C64.description:
Explain the reasons for the rise of nation-states and the effects of nationalism in Europe, North America and
Asia.

8621FB00AECA4C96A94F418236FBD6C5.description:
Trace events, explain the causes, and analyze the outcomes for the Latin American independence
movements of the nineteenth century.

D9EC82D782A54294828EA5B4D8DCDA96.description:
Examine the key causes, events, and consequences of the French Revolution as well as the rise and fall of
Napoleon.

7126F3E3BED3424FBB9F3BEC08C2CAFD.description:
Explain the key ideas of the Enlightenment in European history and describe its impact upon political and
religious thought and culture in Europe and the Americas including the foundation of American government.

D49894B370B94EEDAC9F38C25A44CE83.description: Explain the key developments of the Scientific Revolution and its impact on the world.

DB73F4D2CD804E26B08B09BE5F23F4AD.description: Revolutions, Nationalism, and Imperial Power: 1500 to 1900 CE

1EEF0F714A4447E7BC9D10C6ED123A1E.description:
Describe the progression of events in England that led to constitutional monarchy such as the Magna Carta,
the English Civil War, and the Glorious Revolution of 1688.

D5A42FA0744A434D9B23C94C886926EA.description: Trace the development and impact of absolute monarchies in Europe.

53E93D53214142128656638F77236087.description:
Trace the development of the gunpowder empires such as the Ottoman, Mughal, and Ming empires and their
reaction to Western interaction.

4BD56D1BEB8A41A390726653A00B74F5.description:
Examine the growth and development of the European economic system as a result of exploration and the
growth of mercantilism.

17578814971E4EDFA010BE603767F4CA.description:
Explain consequences of the conquests and colonization as a result of the worldwide voyages of exploration
including the transatlantic slave trade, Columbian Exchange, and the effects on native populations in the
Americas.

3ABE19DD93B74F368238D688E97B4A80.description: Explain the causes of the worldwide voyages of exploration.

94BE2FD9AC5C4C54954D80D0AD65A4E0.description:
Discuss the emergence of nationalism and nation-states as well as the increased impact of the citizen as a
result of the decline of the European medieval period.

E911A15260FB4D558386A8E20F20CB1C.description:
Analyze the factors that led to the rise and spread of the Protestant Reformation, the Catholic CounterReformation,
as well as reforming movements in other religions, including the wars of religion.

AC37C54F528A455D9817BB509978F862.description:
Trace the origins and developments of the European Renaissance and its impact throughout Western
Europe.

1C75570865ED4B77B02340AC0900CB9B.description: The Rise of Western Civilization and Global Interaction: 1300 to 1750 CE

6CE1CB12F62F4FBFA50F513F66648982.description: Examine the development of feudalism in Japan and its impact on Japanese society and government.

3B51013CFEB04522847EDBE2A142254D.description:
Describe and explain the rise, expansion and decline of the Mongol Empire and its consequences for
Eurasian peoples.

19A0199C50C8472F95B50F4F70661706.description: Explain and understand the achievements of the Tang and Song Dynasties.

44BF0AB93CBB49BCA7E5DA673E22C3F3.description: Compare and contrast the developments and achievements of the Maya, Aztec and Inca civilizations.

481EDBD2B80C43269EAADC22B5C11810.description: Examine the key achievements of civilizations in Africa prior to European contact.

C61DA803F0CC4E9FB31881C2FC1DABBF.description:
Describe the improvements in agriculture, the growth of towns, and the commercial revival during the Middle
Ages.

0775BF9611A44739A764DF1C58594604.description:
Explain the cultural, political and religious causes of the Crusades and their consequences for Europe and
Southwest Asia, including the growth in power of the monarchies in Europe.

7492D6603C164FC69C026C74CFCDD02A.description:
Analyze the consequences of the fall of the Western Roman Empire and the development of feudalism and
manorialism on Europe.

16AE63DCBEC04C53BDEF13B9D75EC669.description: Describe the rise and achievements of Charlemagne and the birth of the Holy Roman Empire.

14A6C09ED6E24F128E1B375D9EDD3035.description: Explain the role of Christianity as a unifying force in medieval Europe.

646E9C0E7DF7497A8BC836641D50ADE6.description: Trace the spread of Islam and its impact throughout Southern Europe, Northern Africa and Asia.

76C3CB3F1F81437F8F7109CAE0BFC060.description:
Examine the origins, rise, and spread of Islam including the life of Muhammad, and Islam’s division into the
Sunnis and Shiites.

1F8EF9D11D944F80A3BA41C3FB7284EB.description:
Explain the division between the Eastern and Western branches of Christianity as a result of the Great
Schism of 1054.

FF0917E082C4407B8273B1BE1448887C.description: Explain the rise and achievements of the Byzantine Empire.

FB9B8D6D1B594939A4A73404386AD583.description: Analyze the impact of trade networks such as the Silk Road and Indian Ocean trade network.

F056FC5E71EE42448EA8F984CC0EA474.description: Major Civilizations and Cultural Interactions: c.600 A.D./C.E. to c.1300 A.D./C.E.

732309C018AE48C3A719F761C0888329.description: Trace the developments and achievements of the Qin and Han Dynasties. (Government, Sociology)

7E099B4685A04569A7E4A5F13D0B0A73.description:
Compare and contrast the influence of Confucianism, Taoism, and Legalism on East Asian civilizations.
(Sociology)

F3D27E5C9CDB48218A6D9B4FEAD06DC1.description:
Compare and contrast the influence of Hinduism and Buddhism on civilization in India and Buddhism’s
spread throughout Asia. (Psychology, Sociology)

9648A55940B64B669C80A7269F624DC6.description:
Trace the development and major achievements of civilizations in India such as the Mauryan and Gupta
empires. (Geography, Sociology)

2FBE0AE419E345EFB13DE9988046B715.description:
Examine the significant achievements of the Greeks and Romans and their impact on the modern world.
(Individuals, Society and Culture)

651874BBD3304F3B833553A7D7158E70.description:
Analyze the causes, conditions, and consequences of the decline and fall of the western part of the Roman
Empire.

600BE9901980407799D9D5BC5A9BFCCF.description:
Examine the origins, rise, and spread of Christianity including the life of Jesus, and Christianity’s impact on
the Roman Empire. (Sociology)

0F9D5992EB504E71A858119F152BDA41.description: Trace the changes that culminated in the end of the Republic and the formation of the Roman Empire.

67AD9FFB4B0548BF82491708CE13A993.description: Analyze the development of Roman Republican government and society. (History, Government, Sociology)

E574292B2CC34319AB598EEF9D9A3E24.description:
Describe the rise of Alexander the Great and the influence of Hellenism in Southwest and South Asia,
North Africa, and parts of Europe.

1041287C970A4DE3956447944CA092E8.description:
Examine the development of Greek civilization including differing political and social structures as well as
conflicts such as the Persian and Peloponnesian wars. (Sociology, Economics, Government, Geography)

CC63C4810AC74074A373426C7CB43AC4.description:
Examine the development of Judaism and the civilization of Ancient Israel, including the origins of
monotheism, the significance of the Exodus from Egypt, the Hebrew Bible and the Ten Commandments as
the source of many moral and ethical traditions of Western civilization.

4A41F000C12C43A4BBAB8631A1601EFA.description:
Review the development and key concepts of major world religions and philosophies including Hinduism,
Buddhism, Judaism, Christianity, and Islam. (Sociology)

BB6BE4F410D145ED836047636D94A55E.description: Classical Civilization: c.1000 B.C. / B.C.E. to c.600 A.D. / C.E.

7E4529A9BE104220A7DC5AA2906A06AF.description:
Examine the development and characteristics of early empires such as Assyria, Persia, Israel, Minoan, and
Zhou. (Geography, Sociology)

D8C7258B8CB74DBF8196E905C83D0209.description:
Review the key elements of the development of early river valley civilizations in Mesopotamia, Egypt, the
 Indus River Valley, and Shang China. (Geography, Sociology)

C61B3D2C4A0442A6B6BB0E044A97953D.description:
Identify the key components that make up a civilization and the key differences between civilizations and
other forms of social organization. (Geography, Sociology)

0E4D2EDF8D2C4B29A718CF202D8E8EDA.description:
Describe and evaluate social, cultural, and economic changes of small agriculture communities which led to
 the development of large agricultural settlements such as the movement from hunting and gathering societies
 to civilization. (Economics, Geography)

060693782D9D48E79533417A1BF3B003.description: Ancient Cultures and Civilizations: c.8000 B.C./B.C.E. to c.600 B.C/B.C.E
